Would you like a demotion?

11:27.187 --> 11:28.856
I can arrange that.

11:28.889 --> 11:30.057
I'll do it today.

11:30.090 --> 11:31.058
Yeah, I know you will.

11:31.091 --> 11:32.726
Sure.

11:34.361 --> 11:35.395
Rough night?

11:35.428 --> 11:36.764
Yeah.

11:36.797 --> 11:38.899
But I ain't
complaining, fool.

11:38.932 --> 11:39.900
(chuckles)

11:39.933 --> 11:42.069
Gots to love it.

11:42.102 --> 11:43.536
I don't know who
ordered all this stuff,

11:43.570 --> 11:45.338
but I want it all
86ed out of here.

11:45.372 --> 11:47.174
Yo, what's that green mess,
anyway?

11:47.207 --> 11:49.743
Dad's on a fast for the ASAs,

11:49.777 --> 11:52.345
'cause Mom let him know that
TV puts ten pounds on you.

11:52.379 --> 11:54.514
No, he's doing it
for his health.

11:54.547 --> 11:56.750
Um, so I got a rough script.

11:56.784 --> 11:59.019
Andre's gonna start
with some narration

11:59.052 --> 12:00.220
to set up the scene;

12:00.253 --> 12:01.688
he should be here
in a minute.

12:01.721 --> 12:03.590
(Lucious playing piano)

12:05.959 --> 12:08.395
Dad, that's not it.

12:08.428 --> 12:10.530
You don't think that sounds
played out? It honestly

12:10.563 --> 12:11.698
sounds like you're
trying to make my song

12:11.731 --> 12:12.732
sound like your old song.

12:12.766 --> 12:14.067
Well, if it sounds played out,

12:14.101 --> 12:15.735
it means you wrote
a played out song.

12:15.769 --> 12:16.937
I wrote a played out song?

12:16.970 --> 12:18.405
I'm trying to fix...
No, you don't want
to change it

12:18.438 --> 12:19.606
and you sound...
Listen, I'm not down

12:19.639 --> 12:20.874
with all of this R & B
back and forth.

12:20.908 --> 12:22.109
Mom, where's my verse
supposed to be?

12:22.142 --> 12:23.110
Okay, pause.
I'm supposed to
sing on the bridge?

12:23.143 --> 12:24.211
Pause!

12:24.244 --> 12:25.378
I'm running this.

12:25.412 --> 12:27.080
I got this, and of course

12:27.114 --> 12:28.715
we're gonna find somewhere
for your verse, Hakeem...

12:28.748 --> 12:30.217
and Lucious,
your verse can be

12:30.250 --> 12:31.618
a flip on Jamal's,
and Jamal, it's your song.

12:31.651 --> 12:33.053
JAMAL:
Thank you, Mom,
thank you.

12:33.086 --> 12:34.054
See, it's my song.

12:34.087 --> 12:35.422
You know what?
This ain't working.

12:35.455 --> 12:37.424
I want to go back
to my original plan.

12:37.457 --> 12:39.059
JAMAL:
What original plan, Dad?
Where we do the song

12:39.092 --> 12:40.060
where you accuse us
of biting the hand

12:40.093 --> 12:41.461
that never really fed us?

12:41.494 --> 12:42.796
Oh, you didn't eat?
Nah, he talking
about the song

12:42.830 --> 12:43.931
that he wrote back when
(Cookie sighing)

12:43.964 --> 12:44.932
he thought Mom
was snitch bitch.

12:44.965 --> 12:46.266
(discordant piano note)

12:46.299 --> 12:48.936
Now, y'all sound like
a rack of bitches, okay?

12:48.969 --> 12:49.937
Lucious can sit up here

12:49.970 --> 12:51.304
and take y'all's
jaw jacking,

12:51.338 --> 12:53.140
but I'm not 'cause
I'm running this show.

12:53.173 --> 12:54.942
Excuse me?
Yeah, excuse me.

12:54.975 --> 12:56.910
I busted my ass
to finally get here

12:56.944 --> 12:58.912
and I'll be damned if
I let y'all mess it up.

12:58.946 --> 13:00.413
So put your big
girl drawers on,

13:00.447 --> 13:01.648
'cause we gonna
come together

13:01.681 --> 13:03.116
and do this as a family.

13:03.150 --> 13:04.584
Does anybody here
know what that means?

13:04.617 --> 13:05.819
ANDRE:
That's an
intriguing question...

13:07.988 --> 13:10.690
and I have someone here with me
that might have a point of view.

13:12.459 --> 13:14.427
It's okay, Grandma.

13:14.461 --> 13:16.463
This is your family.

13:25.205 --> 13:26.173
COOKIE:
Lucious...

13:26.206 --> 13:28.308
JAMAL:
Whose grandmother?

13:28.341 --> 13:29.977
What do you mean Grandma?

13:32.479 --> 13:34.447
Who is this lady?

13:34.481 --> 13:36.549
Lucious.

13:40.854 --> 13:42.155
Dwight?

13:44.357 --> 13:46.793
Andre, what's going on?

13:46.826 --> 13:49.196
This is Leah Walker...

13:49.229 --> 13:50.497
Lucious' mother.

13:51.731 --> 13:54.167
Andre,
our grandmother's dead.

13:56.536 --> 13:58.005
(sighs)

13:58.038 --> 14:00.407
ANDRE:
What, you got
nothing to say?

14:02.542 --> 14:04.377
You want to tell
them about how you...

14:04.411 --> 14:05.712
sent her away to a home

14:05.745 --> 14:08.381
for 21 years,
never looked back?

14:08.415 --> 14:10.717
Or how about how you

14:10.750 --> 14:13.653
sent Vernon out there once
a month to pay out hush money

14:13.686 --> 14:14.821
to anybody who knew
who she really was--

14:14.854 --> 14:16.489
how about that one, huh?

14:16.523 --> 14:17.824
Dad, what?

14:17.857 --> 14:19.392
Yeah, that's not true.
It's not.

14:19.426 --> 14:22.095
No, Harper Scott gave me
her files.

14:26.699 --> 14:28.668
Can't lie your way out
of this one, Pop.

14:28.701 --> 14:31.538
(crying)

14:35.608 --> 14:38.045
You have no...

14:38.078 --> 14:39.546
idea what you've done.

14:49.089 --> 14:50.890
I can't believe
that just happened.

14:50.924 --> 14:53.360
Yeah, it's deeper
than we think, too.

14:53.393 --> 14:55.095
You see the look
on his face?

14:55.128 --> 14:56.729
D-MAJOR:
What's good, Lyon brothers?

14:56.763 --> 14:58.565
(phone beeping)
Here to check out
your rehearsal.

14:58.598 --> 15:00.200
Hey, yo, Laura
blowing me up.

15:00.233 --> 15:01.201
Meet you up, bro.
All right.

15:01.234 --> 15:02.202
Baby...

15:02.235 --> 15:03.403
Yo.

15:03.436 --> 15:04.737
Yo, you might not
want to go back there;

15:04.771 --> 15:06.406
Lucious and Cookie
are trying to figure

15:06.439 --> 15:07.774
some things out.
Yeah, well,
maybe I can help.

15:07.807 --> 15:09.376
No, no, it's family stuff.

15:09.409 --> 15:10.777
Besides, you really expect me
to believe that you

15:10.810 --> 15:11.878
only came for rehearsal?

15:11.911 --> 15:13.213
Yeah, that's my job,

15:13.246 --> 15:14.647
but if I'm not needed,
then I'm out.

15:26.593 --> 15:28.228
COOKIE:
Lucious...

15:28.261 --> 15:30.097
Yeah, baby?

15:30.130 --> 15:32.732
Why did you lie?

15:32.765 --> 15:34.968
I didn't lie
about anything.

15:36.603 --> 15:39.406
Then what was that video about?

15:39.439 --> 15:41.908
(sighs)

15:41.941 --> 15:44.144
The truth.

15:44.177 --> 15:46.413
My mother did try and drown me.

15:46.446 --> 15:49.983
She did put a gun to her head
and pulled the trigger,

15:50.017 --> 15:52.952
and told an eight-year-old boy
that it was his fault

15:52.986 --> 15:56.323
she was the way she is.

15:56.356 --> 15:59.359
Just turns out there was
no bullets in the gun.

16:01.194 --> 16:02.762
Well, if she didn't die then...

16:02.795 --> 16:04.464
No...

16:04.497 --> 16:08.201
my mother died the day
that they locked her up.

16:09.636 --> 16:11.804
And then remember
how under Reagan...

16:13.473 --> 16:15.308
...the government took all
the mentally ill patients

16:15.342 --> 16:16.776
and dumped them out
on the street?

16:16.809 --> 16:19.946
Well, one day in front
of 30th Street Station,

16:19.979 --> 16:22.349
I damn near
tripped over her.

16:22.382 --> 16:23.983
Now you and me,
we were on welfare

16:24.017 --> 16:25.452
and had two and a half kids,

16:25.485 --> 16:27.854
we couldn't take care of her
if we wanted to.

16:30.657 --> 16:32.159
You just...

16:32.192 --> 16:34.561
you could have at least
told me about her, Lucious.

16:36.496 --> 16:38.165
(whispering):
I couldn't.

16:38.198 --> 16:39.966
I needed her to stay dead.

16:39.999 --> 16:44.871
That's why I took
Andre to the grave.

16:44.904 --> 16:47.540
He just wouldn't leave
it alone, you know.

16:49.376 --> 16:50.810
But he just doesn't understand.

16:50.843 --> 16:53.746
I mean, none of y'all
understand how...

16:53.780 --> 16:55.548
dangerous she really is.

17:04.957 --> 17:06.593
Why didn't you tell me?
How did you
even find out?

17:06.626 --> 17:07.827
What, you were snooping
through my computer?

17:07.860 --> 17:09.196
It doesn't matter
how I found out.

17:09.229 --> 17:10.663
What matters is, Tiana's
doing a duet with you

17:10.697 --> 17:12.165
on a song you yourself
told me would go platinum.

17:12.199 --> 17:13.166
The producers wanted her.

17:13.200 --> 17:14.033
It was out of my control, babe.

17:14.067 --> 17:15.335
You could have pushed for me.

17:15.368 --> 17:16.769
I bet you never even
brought me up.

17:18.471 --> 17:19.706
Baby...

17:19.739 --> 17:21.007
I love you.

17:21.040 --> 17:22.342
Okay? You know that.

17:22.375 --> 17:23.710
But you can't
automatically think

17:23.743 --> 17:25.178
you're gonna be
on all my duets.

17:25.212 --> 17:28.215
Trust me, there'll be
other opportunities.

17:29.949 --> 17:31.218
I trust you.

17:31.251 --> 17:32.852
I just don't trust Tiana.

17:32.885 --> 17:34.354
She's still feeling you.

17:34.387 --> 17:36.022
So what if she is?

17:36.055 --> 17:37.390
I want you.

17:37.424 --> 17:39.826
*

17:51.938 --> 17:53.706
ANDRE:
I don't trust him, okay?

17:53.740 --> 17:55.442
I think she needs to stay
with us until we find

17:55.475 --> 17:56.443
a permanent situation.

17:56.476 --> 17:57.877
No, Andre,
we're staying in a hotel.

17:57.910 --> 18:00.447
We can get her an
adjoining room, babe.
Oh...

18:00.480 --> 18:02.215
I think we should at least
talk to her caregivers.

18:02.249 --> 18:05.385
I mean, do you even know
who her doctors are?

18:05.418 --> 18:06.719
Great.

18:06.753 --> 18:07.887
(sighs)

18:07.920 --> 18:09.889
RHONDA:
This will be fun.

18:09.922 --> 18:12.058
Come on, Granny Groove.

18:12.091 --> 18:13.926
ANDRE:
What the hell?

18:13.960 --> 18:16.263
THIRSTY:
Whoopsy daisy.

18:16.296 --> 18:18.565
Hey!

18:18.598 --> 18:20.400
Where the hell you think
you're going, man?
LUCIOUS:
Hey, Andre.

18:20.433 --> 18:22.068
No, where you going?
Andre!

18:22.101 --> 18:23.236
Andre, fall back.
Fall back?!

18:23.270 --> 18:24.437
What you talking...
I don't know what

18:24.471 --> 18:26.473
you think you're gonna
get out of this, but that's not

18:26.506 --> 18:27.807
what you want
right now.
You're the one who hid her

18:27.840 --> 18:29.075
from everybody, you did that.
I didn't hide her.

18:29.108 --> 18:30.410
You think she's like you.

18:30.443 --> 18:32.279
She's a completely
different kind of person.

18:32.312 --> 18:33.646
Andre...

18:33.680 --> 18:34.981
she needs to be back
at the home, baby.

18:35.014 --> 18:36.583
You don't know how miserable
she was in that home, Ma.

18:36.616 --> 18:37.750
COOKIE:
She needs to be
with professionals.

18:37.784 --> 18:38.585
You don't know,
you don't know about it.

18:38.618 --> 18:39.586
Grandma, listen...

18:39.619 --> 18:41.421
I got your medicine

18:41.454 --> 18:42.455
and your suitcase with all
your things, all right?

18:42.489 --> 18:43.923
I got plenty of room for you.

18:43.956 --> 18:45.925
ANDRE: We're gonna
go home, okay?
COOKIE: Andre...

18:45.958 --> 18:47.760
I want to go home...
Yeah, we're going home,
we're going home.

18:47.794 --> 18:50.197
...with my Dwight.

19:12.552 --> 19:13.953
Dwight...

19:13.986 --> 19:15.822
I want to go
to bed now.

19:15.855 --> 19:19.359
I'll have the nurse
take you to your room.

19:32.339 --> 19:33.873
Juanita.

19:33.906 --> 19:35.242
Yes, sir.

19:37.844 --> 19:39.979
I want you to make sure

19:40.012 --> 19:42.014
she takes each and
every one of her pills.

19:42.048 --> 19:43.850
Watch her put them
in her mouth.

19:43.883 --> 19:45.818
Check to make sure
she swallowed them.

19:45.852 --> 19:47.487
Remove the phone
out of her room,

19:47.520 --> 19:49.522
and nobody comes to see her
without my permission.

19:49.556 --> 19:52.492
And no matter what, you don't
take your eyes off of her, okay?

19:52.525 --> 19:53.893
Yes, sir.

20:02.369 --> 20:03.503
* I came for blood

20:03.536 --> 20:04.837
* Your days are done

20:04.871 --> 20:06.839
* I came to win,
you came to run... *

20:06.873 --> 20:08.007
I thought we were
going to Lucious'?

20:08.040 --> 20:09.342
You said he wanted
to make a statement.

20:09.376 --> 20:11.244
Can I ask you
something, Ms. Scott?

20:11.278 --> 20:12.379
Why did you become
a journalist?

20:13.380 --> 20:15.348
Because I believe
in the truth.

20:15.382 --> 20:18.084
Hmm, see, that's why
I became an attorney.

20:18.117 --> 20:20.553
The truth is nowhere
near as important

20:20.587 --> 20:22.021
as what you can persuade
people to believe.

20:22.054 --> 20:23.723
THIRSTY:
Case in point...

20:24.791 --> 20:26.092
Do you believe
running your mouth

20:26.125 --> 20:27.427
about Leah Walker
can get you hurt?

20:27.460 --> 20:29.195
Lucious should know that

20:29.228 --> 20:30.763
I can't be threatened or bought.

20:30.797 --> 20:33.165
Mm-hmm.

20:35.935 --> 20:38.605
That's what he thought.

20:38.638 --> 20:40.873
What are you gonna do?

20:40.907 --> 20:43.376
Kill me and leave me
by the side of the road?

20:43.410 --> 20:46.045
I resent that-- I'm a gentleman.

20:46.078 --> 20:47.614
I wouldn't touch
a hair on your head.

20:47.647 --> 20:50.417
* Something's coming alive now
(unlocks)

20:50.450 --> 20:51.551
Bye-bye.

20:51.584 --> 20:54.554
* All the fears just died out

20:54.587 --> 20:55.722
* Now I'm comin' to conquer

20:55.755 --> 20:57.256
* You've awakened a monster

20:57.290 --> 20:59.426
Thanks, Thirsty, appreciate...
* I can feel it inside now

20:59.459 --> 21:01.260
(screaming)
* I came for blood

21:01.294 --> 21:02.795
* Your days are done,
I came to win *

21:02.829 --> 21:03.963
(muffled screaming)
* You came to run

21:03.996 --> 21:05.231
(tires screeching)
* It's all or nothing

21:05.264 --> 21:07.300
* I paid enough,
I've waited up *

21:07.334 --> 21:08.801
* I may erupt,
my way or none *

21:08.835 --> 21:09.936
* It's all or nothing.

21:19.779 --> 21:21.180
Hey, J.

21:22.281 --> 21:23.916
This ain't necessary.

21:23.950 --> 21:26.353
I got the message
loud and clear, so...

21:28.120 --> 21:30.156
What about this message?

21:30.189 --> 21:32.291
Come on, man,
stop playing with me.

21:34.461 --> 21:35.928
I thought you
ain't feeling me.

21:35.962 --> 21:36.996
I'm feeling you.

21:37.029 --> 21:38.465
Why would I not
be feeling you?

21:38.498 --> 21:40.467
Hmm?
'Cause you blew me off
like it was nothing.

21:40.500 --> 21:41.834
We were in a work situation.

21:41.868 --> 21:43.135
I try to keep things
professional, man.

21:45.672 --> 21:47.306
And because you're not out.

21:47.340 --> 21:48.541
Hmm?

21:50.343 --> 21:51.344
I don't think

21:51.378 --> 21:52.845
it's anybody's
business, man.

21:52.879 --> 21:54.280
But it is when you're in
a club with a hot girl,

21:54.313 --> 21:55.515
then it's all of the
paparazzi's business.

21:55.548 --> 21:56.649
Look, you're making
a big deal out of this.

21:56.683 --> 21:57.850
It is a big deal...

21:57.884 --> 21:59.185
to me, it's important.

21:59.218 --> 22:00.620
You know, I worked damn hard

22:00.653 --> 22:01.821
to walk in my truth.

22:03.890 --> 22:05.291
That's why I thought
you would understand

22:05.324 --> 22:07.026
where I'm coming from, man.

22:07.059 --> 22:09.696
It's hard, man.

22:09.729 --> 22:11.297
You know that thing you did
with Skye Summers,

22:11.330 --> 22:12.331
man, I thought
that was so cool...

22:12.365 --> 22:13.633
Derek, that was
completely different.

22:13.666 --> 22:15.134
Yo, man, you should understand
where I'm coming from.

22:15.167 --> 22:16.202
Listen to me, man.
No, stop!

22:16.235 --> 22:18.471
Stop.

22:18.505 --> 22:23.309
Now, I like you
a lot, I do...

22:23.342 --> 22:26.245
but this whole thing...

22:26.278 --> 22:27.480
it's not for me,

22:27.514 --> 22:29.516
so, please...

22:42.028 --> 22:44.397
(jazz playing)

22:53.740 --> 22:55.675
I don't think that whiskey

22:55.708 --> 22:58.377
is a part of your
juicing cleanse.

23:02.549 --> 23:05.518
What are you
afraid of, huh?

23:05.552 --> 23:07.186
She's just a...

23:07.219 --> 23:10.757
feeble, fragile,
little old lady.

23:10.790 --> 23:12.859
So that's what you think, huh?

23:12.892 --> 23:15.261
That's what she wants
everybody to think.

23:15.294 --> 23:16.395
Hmm...

23:20.900 --> 23:22.569
You're afraid...

23:22.602 --> 23:25.371
that if this gets out,
it'll be a scandal.

23:25.404 --> 23:27.406
Yeah, you're afraid you're
gonna lose all that love

23:27.440 --> 23:29.041
you got for "Boom
Boom Boom Boom."

23:29.075 --> 23:32.044
Trust me, this gets out,
it's not good for nobody.

23:32.078 --> 23:34.213
It ain't gonna
get out, Lucious.

23:34.246 --> 23:37.049
Just as long as you do
right by your sons.

23:37.083 --> 23:39.285
So that's what this is about?

23:39.318 --> 23:41.087
Damn ASA performance?

23:41.120 --> 23:43.456
You trying to get me
to do the song

23:43.490 --> 23:44.791
Jamal's way, huh?

23:44.824 --> 23:47.159
This is not about
the ASAs, stupid.

23:47.193 --> 23:50.429
This is about you.

23:50.463 --> 23:52.565
You sitting up here,
acting like you still

23:52.599 --> 23:53.800
in those Philly projects,

23:53.833 --> 23:54.901
when you the king.

23:54.934 --> 23:56.068
You the king
of the world,

23:56.102 --> 23:58.638
and there is
nothing to fear.

23:58.671 --> 24:01.741
Especially not
from your own mama.

24:01.774 --> 24:04.410
Get yourself together.

24:04.443 --> 24:07.514
I'm the one that should
be drinking around here.

24:12.819 --> 24:15.254
CAROL:
Thank you for coming, Candace.

24:15.287 --> 24:16.623
You're welcome.

24:16.656 --> 24:18.424
Uh, Candace, listen,
I really need for you

24:18.457 --> 24:20.927
to keep my kids just
a little while longer.

24:20.960 --> 24:23.162
They need their mother.

24:23.195 --> 24:24.597
Well, you know, I'm about
to get my 90-day chip and...

24:24.631 --> 24:25.798
And?

24:25.832 --> 24:27.600
I just need a little more time

24:27.634 --> 24:29.435
to make things right
with everyone.

24:29.468 --> 24:31.804
What do you mean by that?

24:31.838 --> 24:35.141
I want to tell Cookie...

24:35.174 --> 24:36.442
about what Lucious and I did...

24:36.475 --> 24:37.443
Hell to the no!

24:37.476 --> 24:38.811
No, but come on, I'm not

24:38.845 --> 24:40.613
like y'all;
I can't live with secrets.

24:40.647 --> 24:41.948
It's not a secret.

24:41.981 --> 24:43.616
It's an atomic bomb.

24:43.650 --> 24:45.151
What you gonna say, huh?

24:45.184 --> 24:46.152
"Cookie...

24:46.185 --> 24:47.153
"here's your morning papers,

